## Pipeline Stage Details

| Stage | Trigger | Celery Task | Input | Output | Rate Limit |
|-------|---------|-------------|-------|--------|------------|
| **1. Schedule** | APScheduler interval | — | `sources` table | `run_scraper` messages | Per source `fetch_frequency_hours` |
| **2. Scrape** | `run_scraper.delay()` | `regradar.run_scraper` | Source ID | `List[RawDocument]` | 1 retry, 600s delay |
| **3. Dedup** | Inside `run_scraper` | (same task) | Content hash | New/changed docs only | — |
| **4. LLM Extract** | `process_document.delay()` | `regradar.process_document` | Document ID | `LLMExtractionResult` | **50/hour** |
| **5. CA Review** | Human action (API) | — | Review queue | Approved/Rejected | — |
| **6. Match** | `generate_alerts.delay()` | `regradar.generate_alerts` | ComplianceItem ID | Matched profiles | 2 retries |
| **7. Deliver** | `deliver_alert.delay()` | `regradar.deliver_alert` | Alert ID | DeliveryLogs | 3 retries, 300s delay |

## Task Chaining Pattern

```
APScheduler
    └──▶ run_scraper (for each source)
            └──▶ process_document (for each new/changed doc)
                    └──▶ [HUMAN: CA Review via API]
                            └──▶ generate_alerts_for_item (for each approved item)
                                    └──▶ deliver_alert_task (for each created alert)
```

> [!NOTE]
> The pipeline is **not** a single synchronous chain. Each `└──▶` arrow represents a **separate Celery task** enqueued via `.delay()`. This gives fault isolation — if one LLM call fails, it doesn't block other documents from being processed.
